# Phone Number Provisioning

## POST /numbers/provision

Provisions multiple phone numbers with specified messaging and voice capabilities and assigns them to designated routes.

### Request

#### Headers

```
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {your_api_token}

 ```

#### Body Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `NumberType` | string | Yes | Type of phone number to provision. Valid values: `mvno`, `iot` |
| `MessageType` | string | Yes | Messaging classification. Valid values: `p2p`, `a2p` |
| `MessageEnabled` | boolean | Yes | Whether to enable SMS/MMS messaging capability |
| `VoiceEnabled` | boolean | Yes | Whether to enable voice calling capability |
| `MessageRouteId` | string | Conditional | UUID of the message routing configuration (required if MessageEnabled is true) |
| `VoiceRouteId` | string | Conditional | UUID of the voice routing configuration (required if VoiceEnabled is true) |
| `PhoneNumbers` | array | Yes | List of phone numbers to provision |

> **Important Notes**: 


### Sample Request

``` json
{
    "NumberType": "iot",
    "MessageType": "p2p",
    "MessageEnabled": true,
    "VoiceEnabled": true,
    "MessageRouteId": "MRID-73af1e73-d7b3-4696-bdd9-5b407c96fc8a",
    "VoiceRouteId": "CRID-4dec6beb-3985-444b-8c06-8baa70dc145",
    "PhoneNumbers": [
        {
            "Number": "+12164278934"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233156"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233122"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233111"
        }
    ]
}

 ```

### Responses

#### 200 OK: Success

Returns the order details for the provisioned phone numbers.

``` json
{
    "OrderDate": "2025-05-14T18:56:33.0005512+00:00",
    "OrderId": "JNUOID-ad65e0d6-dbc6-41bd-bc51-736fb6a1e20a",
    "OrderStatus": "Submitted",
    "PhoneNumbersRequested": [
        {
            "Number": "+12164278934"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233156"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233122"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233111"
        }
    ]
}

 ```

##### Response Fields

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `OrderDate` | string | Timestamp when the order was submitted (ISO 8601 format) |
| `OrderId` | string | Unique identifier for the provisioning order |
| `OrderStatus` | string | Current status of the order (e.g., "Submitted", "Processing", "Completed") |
| `PhoneNumbersRequested` | array | List of phone numbers that were requested for provisioning |

#### 400 Bad Request: Validation Error

``` json
{
    "Type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.1",
    "Title": "One or more validation errors occurred.",
    "Status": 400,
    "Errors": {
        "$.NumberType": ["Invalid NumberType and MessageType combination. IOT numbers can only be provisioned with p2p MessageType."]
    },
    "TraceId": "00-1234abcd5678efgh-abcdef123456-00"
}

 ```

#### 401 Unauthorized: Authentication Error

``` json
{
    "Type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235#section-3.1",
    "Title": "Unauthorized",
    "Status": 401,
    "TraceId": "00-1234abcd5678efgh-abcdef123456-00"
}

 ```

### Usage Notes

- Before provisioning, use the `/numbers/availability` endpoint to check if your desired numbers are available.

- Provisioning is an asynchronous process. Check the order status using the returned `OrderId`.

- Both `MessageRouteId` and `VoiceRouteId` must be valid, pre-configured route identifiers in your account.

- All phone numbers in a single request will have the same configuration (NumberType, MessageType, routes).

- Number formatting must be in E.164 format (e.g., +12164278934).


### Try It

```
curl -X POST https://api.example.com/numbers/provision \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_TOKEN" \
  -d '{
    "NumberType": "iot",
    "MessageType": "p2p",
    "MessageEnabled": true,
    "VoiceEnabled": true,
    "MessageRouteId": "MRID-73af1e73-d7b3-4696-bdd9-5b407c96fc8a",
    "VoiceRouteId": "CRID-4dec6beb-3985-444b-8c06-8baa70dc145",
    "PhoneNumbers": [
        {
            "Number": "+12164278934"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233156"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233122"
        },
        {
            "Number": "+12232233111"
        }
    ]
}'

 ```

